Description: Sculptor Paul is reunited with a former great love after a long time, but is much more impressed by his 15-year-old daughter, Laura, who looks like her mother when Paul was in love with her.

Title: What Men Want
Description: A woman is boxed out by the male sports agents in her profession, but gains an unexpected edge over them when she develops the ability to hear men's thoughts.

Title: Phantasm
Description: A teenage boy and his friends face off against a mysterious grave robber, known only as the Tall Man, who employs a lethal arsenal of unearthly weapons.

Title: Point Blank
Description: After being double-crossed and left for dead, a mysterious man named Walker single-mindedly tries to retrieve the money that was stolen from him.

Title: Await Further Instructions
Description: A family's Christmas takes a strange turn when they awake to find themselves trapped inside and begin receiving mysterious instructions through the television.

Title: Punisher: War Zone
Description: Frank Castle, known as the Punisher, ruthlessly demolishes organized crime, but it starts an even bigger war.

Title: The Claus Family 2
Description: Jules Claus has embraced Christmas again and is getting ready for the busiest time of the year together with grandpa Noël. Everything seems to go according to plan, until Jules receives a very special letter with an intriguing question.

Title: Godzilla 2000: Millennium
Description: An independent group of researchers actively track Godzilla as a giant meteor is discovered. The mysterious rock begins to levitate as its true intentions for the world and Godzilla are revealed.

Title: A Perfect Ending
Description: Rebecca has a very unusual secret, one that not even her best friends know about. The last person on earth she expects to reveal it to is a high priced escort named Paris.

Title: Yaariyan 2
Description: After moving to Mumbai, three cousins experience difficulties in their romantic relationships.

Title: Student of the Year 2
Description: A student must face off against bullies and overcome hurdles, both academic and romantic, to win his college's coveted Student of the Year trophy.

Title: The Duke of Burgundy
Description: A woman who studies butterflies and moths tests the limits of her relationship with her lesbian lover.

Title: Almost Heroes
Description: Two bumbling explorers hope to beat Lewis & Clarke to the Pacific Ocean as they race across America's western frontier in the early 1800's.

Title: Senseless
Description: A student gets his senses enhanced by an experimental drug. But abuse is not an option.

Title: Pontypool
Description: A radio host interprets the possible outbreak of a deadly virus which infects the small Ontario town he is stationed in.

Title: Three Godfathers
Description: Three fugitives risk their lives to bring a newborn baby out of the desert to safety.

Title: Albert Brooks: Defending My Life
Description: A documentary about the comedian and filmmaker Albert Brooks which includes interviews from Sharon Stone, Larry David, James L Brooks, Conan O'Brien, Sarah Silverman and Jonah Hill.

Title: Puncture
Description: A David and Goliath law drama about a drug-addicted lawyer who takes on a health supply corporation while battling his own personal demons.

Title: The Philadelphia Experiment
Description: A United States Navy destroyer escort participates in a Navy "invisibility" experiment that inadvertently sends two sailors forty years into the future.

Title: War Machine
Description: An idiosyncratic general confronts opposition from enemies, allies, and bureaucrats while leading a massive rebuilding operation in Afghanistan.

Title: Satantango
Description: On the eve of a large payment, residents of a collapsing collective farm see their plans turn into desolation when they discover that Irimiás, a former co-worker who they thought was dead, is returning to the community.

Title: Kinsey
Description: A look at the life of Alfred Kinsey, a pioneer in the area of human sexuality research, whose 1948 publication "Sexual Behavior in the Human Male" was one of the first recorded works that saw science address sexual behavior.

Title: The Last Right
Description: A fateful exchange on a flight has consequences for Daniel Murphy. He's left in charge of a corpse of someone he never knew. He is persuaded to take on the challenge of getting a coffin from his family home in Clonakilty to Rathlin Island.

Title: Pride and Glory
Description: A family's moral codes are tested when Ray Tierney investigates a case that reveals an incendiary police corruption scandal involving his own brother-in-law. For Ray, the truth is revelatory, a Pandora's Box that threatens to upend not only the Tierney legacy but the entire NYPD.

Title: Buddy Games
Description: A group of friends reunite to play The Buddy Games, a wild assortment of absurd physical and mental challenges. In the process, they'll heal old wounds, right past wrongs and figure out the true meaning of friendship...or die trying.

Title: Unleashed
Description: A man enslaved by the mob since childhood and raised into behaving like a human attack dog escapes his captors and attempts to start a new life.

Title: Dave
Description: An uncanny Presidential lookalike named Dave is recruited by the Secret Service to become a momentary stand-in for the President of the United States.

Title: Hamburger Hill
Description: A very realistic interpretation of one of the bloodiest battles of the Vietnam War.

Title: Baby Shark's Big Movie!
Description: Baby Shark is the catchiest fish in the sea, so evil singer Stariana devises a plan to steal his musical power.

Title: Sex for Sale
Description: Three smugglers transport firearms and drugs between Hong Kong and Zhuhai, but most of their illegal activities were raided by Chinese police officers.

Title: Toscana
Description: When a Danish chef travels to Tuscany to sell his father's business, he meets a local woman who inspires him to rethink his approach to life and love.

Title: Bill & Ted's Bogus Journey
Description: A tyrant from the future creates evil android doubles of Bill and Ted and sends them back to eliminate the originals.

Title: A Passage to India
Description: Cultural mistrust and false accusations doom a friendship in British colonial India between an Indian doctor, an Englishwoman engaged to marry a city magistrate, and an English educator.

Title: Artemis Fowl
Description: Artemis Fowl, a young criminal prodigy, hunts down a secret society of fairies to find his missing father.

Title: Chaos
Description: Two cops, a rookie and a grizzled vet, pursue an accomplished bank robber.

Title: Ur spår
Description: A mid-age hipster in Stockholm is a training freak and trains for the 90 km ski race Vasaloppet. His sister is the opposite, no job, drinks but has a daughter. Suddenly secrets reveals and promises are made.

Title: Nionde kompaniet
Description: A group of army conscripts realize that the army has vast resources that don't get used as much as they could. Using army material, they start to do services for people in the neighborhood. More and more money is exchanged, more and more people get involved, but when will someone reveal the truth to someone who they can't pay?

Title: The Killer Inside Me
Description: A West Texas Deputy Sheriff is slowly unmasked as a psychotic killer.

Title: Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas
Description: The sailor of legend is framed by the goddess Eris for the theft of the Book of Peace and must travel to her realm at the end of the world to retrieve it and save the life of his childhood friend Prince Proteus.

Title: Fantastic Voyage
Description: When a blood clot renders a scientist comatose, a submarine and its crew are shrunk and injected into his bloodstream in order to save him.

Title: Wonderland
Description: In the police investigation of a brutal crime scene, one man was at the center of it all: legendary porn star John Holmes.

Title: Victoria
Description: Thirtysomething lawyer Victoria is struggling with her past and looking for stability and true love in her life. Finally she realizes that love should not always be sought.

Title: Antebellum
Description: Successful author Veronica Henley finds herself trapped in a horrifying reality and must uncover the mind-bending mystery before it's too late.

Title: The Unknown Country
Description: An unexpected invitation rushes a grieving young woman into a lonely road trip through the American Midwest towards the border between Texas and Mexico.

Title: The Apology
Description: Twenty years after the disappearance of her daughter, a recovering alcoholic is preparing to host her family's Christmas celebration when her estranged ex-brother-in-law arrives unannounced, bearing nostalgic gifts and a heavy secret.

Title: Once Upon a Time in Anatolia
Description: A group of men set out in search of a dead body in the Anatolian steppes.

Title: King Solomon's Mines
Description: Fortune hunter Allan Quatermain teams up with a resourceful woman to help her find her missing father lost in the wilds of 1900s Africa while being pursued by hostile tribes and a rival German explorer.

Title: Chowchilla
Description: Go behind the headlines to explore the strangest mass kidnapping in history, with exclusive interviews from those who lived through it.

Title: The Starling
Description: After Lilly suffers a loss, a combative Starling takes nest beside her quiet home. The feisty bird taunts and attacks the grief-stricken Lilly. On her journey to expel the Starling, she rediscovers her will to live and capacity for love.

Title: A Place in the Sun
Description: A poor boy gets a job working for his rich uncle and ends up falling in love with two women.

Title: Two Night Stand
Description: A snowstorm forces two people who made an online connection to unwillingly extend their one-night stand as the blizzard goes through the night.

Title: Shallow Grave
Description: Three friends discover their new flatmate dead but loaded with cash.

Title: Carry on Cruising
Description: Captain Crowther's lot is not a happy one! Five of his crew have to be replaced and at such short notice before the voyage begins there isn't much to choose from. Not only does he get the five most incompetent shipmates ever to sail the seven seas, but the passengers turn out to be a rather strange bunch too. The SS Happy Wanderer will never be the same.

Title: The Vanishing
Description: Three lighthouse keepers on the remote Flannan Isles find a hidden trunk of gold, leading to their mysterious disappearance.

Title: Two Lovers
Description: A Brooklyn-set romantic drama about a bachelor torn between the family friend his parents wish he would marry and his beautiful but volatile new neighbor.

Title: Stone Cold
Description: A tough Alabama cop is blackmailed by the FBI into going undercover in a violent Mississippi biker gang.

Title: The Divide
Description: Survivors of a nuclear attack are grouped together for days in the basement of their apartment building, where fear and dwindling supplies wear away at their dynamic.

Title: Begotten
Description: Presented in a surreal, gory and entirely visual manner, Begotten tells of the death of religion, the abuse of nature by Man and a nihilistic outlook on what life ultimately is.

Title: Honey
Description: Honey is a sexy, tough music video choreographer who shakes up her life after her mentor gives her an ultimatum: sleep with him or be blacklisted within their industry.

Title: The Girl Who Kicked the Hornet's Nest
Description: Lisbeth is recovering in a hospital and awaiting trial for three murders when she is released. Mikael must prove her innocence, but Lisbeth must be willing to share the details of her sordid experiences with the court.

Title: Doi Boy
Description: Sorn, an ethnic Shan sex worker, tries to build a future in Chiang Mai, Thailand, as a refugee far from home, but he is drawn into a complex relationship with a client investigating a political activist.

Title: In Her Shoes
Description: Strait-laced Rose breaks off relations with her party girl sister, Maggie, over an indiscretion involving Rose's boyfriend. The chilly atmosphere is broken with the arrival of Ella, the grandmother neither sister knew existed.

Title: The Great Train Robbery
Description: England, 1850s. A master criminal aims to rob a train of a large sum of gold. Security is incredibly tight and the task seems an impossible one. However, he has a plan and just the right people to carry it out.

Title: Elizabeth: The Golden Age
Description: A mature Queen Elizabeth endures multiple crises late in her reign including court intrigues, an assassination plot, the Spanish Armada, and romantic disappointments.

Title: The Last Legion
Description: As the Roman empire crumbles, young Romulus Augustus flees the city and embarks on a perilous voyage to Britain to track down a legion of supporters.

Title: Myra Breckinridge
Description: After undergoing gender reassignment surgery, an aspiring actress travels to Hollywood, where she also wants to make a claim on her wealthy uncle's estate.

Title: Chasing Liberty
Description: Anna wants to be like other girls her age (18): date a guy etc. but she's the US president's daughter and always guarded. In Prague he breaks his promise of only 2 agents following her to a concert and she runs away with Ben to see Europe.

Title: Along for the Ride
Description: The summer before college Auden meets the mysterious Eli, a fellow insomniac. While the seaside town of Colby sleeps, the two embark on a nightly quest to help Auden experience the fun, carefree teen life she never knew she wanted.

Title: Mamonas Assassinas: O Filme
Description: The life and times of comedy rock band Mamonas Assassinas, from their beginning to their breakthrough in the late 1990s.

Title: Tin & Tina
Description: After a tragic miscarriage, Lola and her husband Adolfo adopt Tin and Tina, a lovely brother and sister with an ultra-catholic education that makes them interpret Holy Bible verbatim.

Title: Resistance
Description: The story of mime Marcel Marceau as he works with a group of Jewish boy scouts and the French Resistance to save the lives of ten thousand orphans during World War II.

Title: The Storied Life of A.J. Fikry
Description: A.J. Fikry's wife has died, his bookstore is in trouble, and now his prized rare edition of Poe poems has been stolen. However, when a mysterious package appears, its arrival gives him the chance to start his life over and see things anew.

Title: Galaxy of Terror
Description: A ragtag spaceship crew sent on a rescue mission encounter a formidable enemy, their worst fears projected by their own imaginations.

Title: How Green Was My Valley
Description: At the turn of the century in a Welsh mining village, the Morgans, he stern, she gentle, raise coal-mining sons and hope their youngest will find a better life.

Title: Luce
Description: A married couple is forced to reckon with their idealized image of their son, adopted from war-torn Eritrea, after an alarming discovery by a devoted high school teacher threatens his status as an all-star student.

Title: Dreamland
Description: A teenager's adventures as a bounty hunter take an unexpected twist.

Title: The Way of the Wind
Description: A retelling of several episodes in the life of Jesus.

Title: Spanglish
Description: A woman and her daughter emigrate from Mexico for a better life in America, where they start working for a family whose patriarch is a newly celebrated chef with an insecure wife.

Title: Everly
Description: A kidnapped woman faces down hitmen sent by a mob boss/her captor while trying to protect her family from his wrath.

Title: Maps to the Stars
Description: A tour into the heart of a Hollywood family chasing celebrity, one another and the relentless ghosts of their pasts.

Title: Lord of the Flies
Description: Schoolboys marooned on a Pacific island create their own savage civilization.

Title: Official Competition
Description: A wealthy businessman hires a famous filmmaker to help make a smash hit film.

Title: Untamed Heart
Description: A waitress hardly notices a shy busboy who secretly loves her; until one night she's attacked and he comes to her rescue. From there a relationship sparks but one secret could mean disaster for these fated lovers.

Title: Gingerdead Man vs Evil Bong
Description: The Gingerdead Man seeks revenge against Sarah Leigh for causing him to live his life in the body of a gingerbread man. Her only hope is to team up with Larnell who has problems of his own in the form of a magical talking bong named Eebee.

Title: Switch
Description: A sexist womanizer is killed by one of his former lovers and then reincarnated as a woman.

Title: The Secret Life of Bees
Description: In 1964, a teenage girl in search of the truth about her mother runs away to a small town in South Carolina and finds a family of independent women who can connect her to her past.

Title: Detroit
Description: Fact-based drama set during the 1967 Detroit riots in which a group of rogue police officers respond to a complaint with retribution rather than justice on their minds.

Title: American Ultra
Description: A stoner - who is in fact a government agent - is marked as a liability and targeted for extermination. But he's too well-trained and too high for them to handle.

Title: Appassionata
Description: A married dentist gets embroiled in a sexual affair with his teenage daughter's best friend. Meanwhile, his wife's mental health is deteriorating, and his daughter is desperate for an affair of her own.

Title: Comet
Description: Set in a parallel universe, Comet bounces back and forth over the course of an unlikely but perfectly paired couple's six-year relationship.

Title: Exotica
Description: A man plagued by neuroses frequents the club Exotica in an attempt to find solace, but even there his past is never far away.

Title: Shall We Dance
Description: A romantic comedy where a bored, overworked Estate Lawyer, upon first sight of a beautiful instructor, signs up for ballroom dancing lessons.

Title: Greedy People
Description: Follows the residents of a small island town who must navigate a sensational murder and the discovery of a million dollars, a series of increasingly bad decisions upend the once peaceful community.

Title: Dodge City
Description: A Texas cattle agent witnesses first hand, the brutal lawlessness of Dodge City and takes the job of sheriff to clean the town up.

Title: The War of the Worlds
Description: A small town in California is attacked by Martians, beginning a worldwide invasion.

Title: Tales from the Crypt
Description: Five strangers get lost in a crypt and, after meeting the mysterious Crypt Keeper, receive visions of how they will die.

Title: Revenge
Description: A retired US Navy pilot comes to Mexico, where he falls in love with the wife of a powerful businessman. The consequences will be cruel and unforeseen.

Title: Personal Shopper
Description: A personal shopper in Paris refuses to leave the city until she makes contact with her twin brother who previously died there. Her life becomes more complicated when a mysterious person contacts her via text message.

Title: A Teacher
Description: A high school teacher in Austin, Texas takes sexual advantage over one of her students. Her life begins to unravel as the details of the relationship are exposed.

Title: Monos
Description: On a remote mountaintop, eight kids with guns watch over a hostage and a conscripted milk cow.

Title: The Christmas Miracle of Jonathan Toomey
Description: When a heartbroken boy loses the precious wooden treasure that links him to his dead father, his worried mother convinces a carver to create a replacement.

Title: Rio Grande
Description: A cavalry officer posted on the Rio Grande is confronted with murderous raiding Apaches, a son who's a risk-taking recruit and his wife from whom he has been separated for many years.

Title: Freaked
Description: A vain actor, his best friend, and an activist end up at a mutant freak farm run by a weirdo scientist.

Title: Amarcord
Description: A series of comedic and nostalgic vignettes set in a 1930s Italian coastal town.

Title: The Seven Year Itch
Description: When his family goes away for the summer, a hitherto faithful husband with an overactive imagination is tempted by a beautiful neighbor.

Title: Elektra Luxx
Description: Life for porn actress Elektra Luxx gets turned upside down when she finds out she's pregnant.

Title: Poltergeist II: The Other Side
Description: The Freeling family have a new house, but their troubles with supernatural forces don't seem to be over.

Title: Frankenhooker
Description: A medical student sets out to recreate his decapitated fiancée by building her a new body made of Manhattan street prostitutes.

Title: Carry on Cowboy
Description: Stodge City is in the grip of the Rumpo Kid and his gang. Mistaken identity again takes a hand as a "sanitary engineer" (plumber) by the name of Marshal P. Knutt is mistaken for a law marshal! Being the conscientious sort, Marshal tries to help the town get rid of Rumpo, and a showdown is inevitable. Marshal has two aids - revenge-seeking Annie Oakley and his sanitary expertise...

Title: Fist Fight
Description: When one school teacher unwittingly causes another teacher's dismissal, he is challenged to an after-school fight.

Title: Jobs
Description: The story of Steve Jobs' ascension from college dropout into one of the most revered creative entrepreneurs of the 20th century.

Title: Regression
Description: A detective and a psychoanalyst uncover evidence of a satanic cult while investigating a young woman's terrifying past.

Title: The Physician
Description: In 11th-century Persia, a surgeon's apprentice disguises himself as a Jew to study at a school that does not admit Christians.

Title: Tales from the Darkside: The Movie
Description: To stall a witch plotting to eat him, a boy reads her horror tales dealing with a collegian's resurrection of a mummy, a murderous cat, and an artist's pact with a gargoyle.

Title: Sundown
Description: Neil and Alice Bennett are the core of a wealthy family on vacation in Mexico until a distant emergency cuts their trip short. When one relative disrupts the family's tight-knit order, simmering tensions rise to the fore.

Title: The Least of These: A Christmas Story
Description: A charming Christmas tale of hope, forgiveness, and faith that centers around a single mom, her seven-year-old daughter, and a Salvation Army Santa Claus.

Title: Nativity Rocks!
Description: The staff and students of St Bernadette's Primary School in Coventry audition for a place in a rock-musical competition.

Title: Buttons, A New Musical Film
Description: Follow the heartwarming journey of two orphan girls whose only wish is to find a home for Christmas. With a little help from their guardian angels (Dick Van Dyke and Dame Angela Lansbury), they discover miracles can happen when you believe.

Title: Above Majestic
Description: A look at the origins, history and conspiracies behind the "Majestic 12", a clandestine group of military and corporate figureheads charged with reverse-engineering extraterrestrial technology.

Title: The Zero Theorem
Description: A hugely talented but socially isolated computer operator is tasked by Management to prove the Zero Theorem: that the universe ends as nothing, rendering life meaningless. But meaning is what he already craves.

Title: Let Them All Talk
Description: A famous author goes on a cruise trip with her friends and nephew in an effort to find fun and happiness while she comes to terms with her troubled past.

Title: War Room
Description: A seemingly perfect family looks to fix their problems with the help of Miss Clara, an older, wiser woman.

Title: Iron Will
Description: A brave young man is thrust into adulthood as he and his courageous team of sled dogs embark on a grueling and treacherous cross-country marathon.

Title: Men at Work
Description: Two garbage men uncover a conspiracy involving illegal toxic waste dumping and decide to bring the whole operation down.

Title: Assault on Precinct 13
Description: A police sergeant must rally the cops and prisoners together to protect themselves on New Year's Eve, just as corrupt policeman surround the station with the intent of killing all to keep their deception in the ranks.

Title: The Iron Lady
Description: An elderly Margaret Thatcher talks to the imagined presence of her recently deceased husband as she struggles to come to terms with his death while scenes from her past life, from girlhood to British prime minister, intervene.

Title: Europa: The Last Battle
Description: Documentary about the origins of World War II.

Title: Dodgeball 2
Description: Plot is unknown at this time.

Title: Repmånad eller Hur man gör pojkar av män
Description: Jonsson is called back for refresher training. He meets Lövgren, Larsson and others who aren't very serious but instead, see it as an opportunity to have fun for a month away from work.

Title: Hobson's Choice
Description: Widower Henry Hobson refuses to let his three daughters get married because he doesn't want to pay settlements, so they'll just have to outsmart him.

Title: King of Thieves
Description: A true crime movie about a crew of retired crooks who pull off a major heist in London's jewelry district. What starts off as their last criminal hurrah, quickly turns into a brutal nightmare due to greed.

Title: Stay Alive
Description: For a group of teens, the answer to the mysterious death of their old friend lies within the world of an online video game based on the true story of an ancient noblewoman known as the Blood Countess.

Title: Christmas with the Knightlys
Description: Georgia Jackson hopes to put on a Christmas showcase with her students, but finds herself in the spotlight when in exchange for a new community center she agrees to pose as the girlfriend of Chase Knightly, the famous son of a billionaire.

Title: Danger Close
Description: In August 1966, in a Vietnamese rubber plantation called Long Tan, 108 young and inexperienced Australian and New Zealand soldiers are fighting for their lives against 2500 North Vietnamese and Viet Cong soldiers.

Title: Underdog
Description: A Beagle must use his newly-bestowed superpowers to defend Capitol City from mad scientist Simon Barsinister.

Title: Beauty Shop
Description: A determined hairstylist (Queen Latifah) competes with her former boss (Kevin Bacon) after opening her own business in Atlanta.

Title: Xanadu
Description: A struggling artist living in Los Angeles meets a girl who may hold the key to his happiness.

Title: Over the Edge
Description: A group of bored teenagers rebels against authority in the community of New Granada after the death of one of their own.

Title: Moonwalker
Description: Anthology movie by, and starring, Michael Jackson in his prime, combining a number of music videos from his bestselling "Bad" album with a fantasy tale of Michael's confrontation with a ruthless drug dealer known as Mr. Big.

Title: The Day of the Beast
Description: Bent on committing as many sins as possible to avert the birth of the beast, a Catholic priest teams up with a Black Metal aficionado and an Italian connoisseur of the occult. Now, he must become an unrelenting sinner. Is there still hope?

Title: Tulip Fever
Description: An artist falls for a young married woman while he's commissioned to paint her portrait during the Tulip mania of seventeenth century Amsterdam.

Title: Mandingo
Description: An 1840s slaveowner trains one of his slaves to be a bare-knuckle fighter.

Title: Last Man Standing
Description: A drifting gunslinger-for-hire finds himself in the middle of an ongoing war between the Irish and Italian mafia in a Prohibition era ghost town.

Title: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre 2
Description: A radio host is victimized by the cannibal family as a former Texas Marshal hunts them.

Title: There's Someone Inside Your House
Description: The graduating class at Osborne High is being targeted by a masked assailant, intent on exposing the darkest secret of each victim, and only a group of misfit outsiders can stop the killings.

Title: Barbershop
Description: A day in the life of a South Side Chicago barbershop.

Title: Dead Man Down
Description: In New York City, a crime lord's right-hand man is helped by a woman seeking retribution.

Title: Lock Up
Description: With only six months left of his sentence, inmate Frank Leone is transferred from a minimum security prison to a maximum security prison by a vindictive warden.

Title: Bolero
Description: Set in the 1920s, a young woman sets out to lose her virginity. Her mission leads her to a Moroccan sheikh and a Spanish bullfighter.

Title: Christmas Carol: The Movie
Description: Old bitter miser Ebenezer Scrooge (Simon Callow) who makes excuses for his uncaring nature learns real compassion when three ghosts visit him on Christmas Eve.

Title: Super Dark Times
Description: Teenagers Zach and Josh have been best friends their whole lives, but when a gruesome accident leads to a cover-up, the secret drives a wedge between them and propels them down a rabbit hole of escalating paranoia and violence.

Title: Silent Night, Bloody Night
Description: A man inherits a mansion which once was a mental home. He visits the place and begins to investigate some crimes that happened in old times, scaring the people living in the region.

Title: Immaculate
Description: Cecilia a woman of devout faith is warm welcomed to the picture-perfect Italian countryside where she is offered a new role at an illustrious convent. But it becomes clearer to Cecilia that her new home harbors dark and horrifying secrets.

Title: A Dog's Way Home
Description: A female dog travels four hundred miles in search of her owner throughout a Colorado wilderness.

Title: The Adventures of Rocky & Bullwinkle
Description: When enemies Boris, Natasha, and Fearless Leader escape into the real world with a nefarious scheme, Rocky and Bullwinkle do the same, and team up with a young F.B.I. Agent to stop the trio.

Title: She's Funny That Way
Description: On the set of a playwright's new project, a love triangle forms between his wife, her ex-lover and the call-girl-turned-actress cast in the production.

Title: Spellbound
Description: A psychiatrist protects the identity of an amnesia patient accused of murder while attempting to recover his memory.

Title: The Man Who Knew Too Little
Description: Wallace Ritchie is mistaken for a spy and must stop a plot to assassinate international leaders at a banquet.

Title: Nightwatch
Description: A law student, who takes a job as a night watchman at a morgue, begins to discover clues that implicate him as the suspect of a series of murders.

Title: Message in a Bottle
Description: A woman discovers a tragic love letter in a bottle on a beach, and is determined to track down its author.

Title: Bringing Back Christmas
Description: Daniel is fired right before his son's expensive surgery. An angel takes him on a journey back in time to witness the trials of Joseph and Mary before the very first Christmas, reminding him how God's love can carry him through anything .

Title: The Current War: Director's Cut
Description: The dramatic story of the cutthroat race between electricity titans Thomas A. Edison and George Westinghouse to determine whose electrical system would power the modern world.

Title: The Clan of the Cave Bear
Description: A young Cro-Magnon woman is raised by Neanderthals.

Title: Diary of a Wimpy Kid
Description: Greg Heffley is an ambitious kid with an active imagination and big plans to be rich and famous. The problem is that he has to survive middle school first.

Title: Accident Man
Description: Mike is a tough hitman, who makes his hits look like accidents or suicide. He's in a gang of hitmen, each with his own style. When his loved ex is killed, Mike looks for those responsible.

Title: Stars at Noon
Description: A young American journalist stranded in present-day Nicaragua falls for an enigmatic Englishman who seems like her best chance of escape. She soon realizes, however, that he may be in even greater danger than she is.

Title: Runway 34
Description: Inspired by true incidents, "Runway 34" revolves around Captain Vikrant Khanna played by Ajay Devgn, a flying prodigy, whose flight takes a mysterious course after take-off from an international destination.

Title: Kingdom
Description: In ancient China, a young boy dreams of becoming the greatest general of the Qin Kingdom.

Title: Flower
Description: A sexually curious teen forms an unorthodox kinship with her mentally unstable stepbrother.

Title: Watching the Detectives
Description: A film noir buff to the extreme is given a taste of his own medicine and has his life turned upside down by a kooky femme fatale with a big adventure in mind. Sometimes love is stranger than fiction.

Title: Irresistible
Description: A Democratic strategist helps a retired veteran run for mayor in a small, conservative Midwest town.

Title: Miracle in Cell No. 7
Description: A story about the love between a mentally-ill father and his lovingly adorable daughter.

Title: Anomalisa
Description: A man crippled by the mundanity of his life experiences something out of the ordinary.

Title: Dragonslayer
Description: A young wizarding apprentice is sent to kill a dragon which has been devouring girls from a nearby kingdom.

Title: The Lady in the Van
Description: A man forms an unexpected bond with a transient woman living in her van that's parked in his driveway.

Title: Going the Distance
Description: In order to prevent a recent high school graduate from getting engaged, two friends intervene by taking him on a cross-country road trip.

Title: Christmas Staycation
Description: When a family can't be together on Christmas, they bring their dysfunctional family Christmas online.

Title: Waiting for Guffman
Description: An aspiring director and the marginally talented amateur cast of a hokey small-town Missouri musical production go overboard when they learn that someone from Broadway will be in attendance.

Title: Smoking Causes Coughing
Description: A group of vigilantes called the "tobacco-forces" is falling apart. To rebuild team spirit, their leader suggests that they meet for a week-long retreat, before returning to save the world.

Title: The Company You Keep
Description: After a journalist discovers his identity, a former Weather Underground activist goes on the run.

Title: Breakfast on Pluto
Description: In the 1970s, a young trans woman, Patrick "Kitten" Braden, comes of age by leaving her Irish town for London, in part to look for her mother and in part because her gender identity is beyond the town's understanding.

Title: Infiesto
Description: Two detectives are called to a small mining town in the Asturian mountains where a young woman who had been left for dead for months has suddenly appeared, leaving the detectives to question what dark forces are at work.

Title: Driven
Description: A young hot shot driver is in the middle of a championship season and is coming apart at the seams. A former CART champion is called in to give him guidance.

Title: Rebel
Description: A portrayal of a family torn apart over a little Muslim boy's future.

Title: Cannonball Run II
Description: The original characters from The Cannonball Run (1981) race across the country once more in various cars and trucks.

Title: The Mechanic
Description: An aging hitman befriends a young man who wants to be a professional killer. Eventually it becomes clear that someone has betrayed them.

Title: Freaky Friday
Description: A mother and daughter find their personalities switched and have to live each other's lives on one strange Friday.

Title: Until the End of the World
Description: In 1999, Claire's life is forever changed after she survives a car crash. She rescues Sam and starts traveling around the world with him. Writer Eugene follows them and writes their story, as a way of recording dreams is being invented.

Title: Replicas
Description: A scientist becomes obsessed with bringing back his family members who died in a traffic accident.

Title: Play Misty for Me
Description: The life of a disc jockey is turned upside down after a romantic encounter with an obsessed fan.

Title: We Are Marshall
Description: When a plane crash claims the lives of members of the Marshall University football team and some of its fans, the team's new coach and his surviving players try to keep the football program alive.

Title: Cruella 2
Description: Plot under wraps. Sequel to 2021 movie "Cruella".

Title: Marty
Description: A middle-aged butcher and a school teacher who have given up on the idea of love meet at a dance and fall for each other.

Title: Scarlet Diva
Description: A young Italian actress embarks on a self-destructive spree of sex, drugs and other excess while doing some soul searching to find the path for redemption.

Title: The Miseducation of Cameron Post
Description: In 1993, a teenage girl is forced into a gay conversion therapy center by her conservative guardians.

Title: Winchester
Description: Ensconced in her sprawling San Jose, California mansion, eccentric firearm heiress Sarah Winchester (Dame Helen Mirren) believes she is haunted by the souls of people killed by the Winchester repeating rifle.

Title: Strike Up the Band
Description: A high-school boy wants to become a professional musician, and his gal pal wants to become his best girl. They work together staging big-band shows with fellow classmates in the hopes of hitting it big.

Title: Running on Empty
Description: The eldest son of a fugitive family comes of age and wants to live his own life.

Title: Cindy La Regia
Description: When Cindy decides that she doesn't want to marry her boyfriend, she runs to Mexico City, where new friendships and unexpected paths teach her that there are many more possibilities for her life and talent than she thought.

Title: Zara Hatke Zara Bachke
Description: Kapil and Somya are a happily married couple from Indore who live in a joint family and decide to get a divorce one fine day. Things don't go as planned as their family gets to know of it, and thus begins a comedy of errors.

Title: Pennies from Heaven
Description: Larry Poole, in prison on a false charge, promise an inmate that when he gets out he will look up and help out a family. The family turns out to be a young girl, Patsy Smith, and her elderly grandfather who need lots of help.

Title: Beirut
Description: Caught in the crossfires of civil war, CIA operatives must send a former U.S. diplomat to negotiate for the life of a friend he left behind.

Title: Igby Goes Down
Description: A young man's peculiar upbringing renders him unable to competently cope with the struggle of growing up.

Title: The Ladykillers
Description: An eccentric, if not charming Southern professor and his crew pose as a classical ensemble in order to rob a casino, all under the nose of his unsuspecting but sharp old landlady.

Title: Greenberg
Description: A man from Los Angeles, who moved to New York years ago, returns to L.A. to figure out his life while he house-sits for his brother. He soon sparks with his brother's assistant.

Title: Squealer
Description: When a local cop and an overzealous social-worker follow clues on missing persons cases around town, stomach-turning discoveries are unearthed on a pig farm, where the town butcher has been slaughtering more than livestock.

Title: Trial by Fire
Description: The tragic and controversial story of Cameron Todd Willingham, who was sentenced to death in Texas for killing his three children even after scientific evidence and expert testimony bolstered his claims of innocence.

Title: Private Resort
Description: The story of two adolescent boys who are guests at a Florida resort for the week-end. Their only interest is, of course, chasing girls, but fate has much more in store for them.

Title: Mission to Mars
Description: When the first manned mission to Mars meets with a catastrophic and mysterious disaster after reporting an unidentified structure, a rescue mission is launched to investigate the tragedy and bring back any survivors.

Title: The Indian in the Cupboard
Description: Omri, a young boy growing up in Brooklyn, receives an odd variety of presents for his birthday: a wooden cupboard from his older brother, a set of antique keys from his mother, and a plastic Indian from his best friend, Patrick.

Title: The Brave One
Description: Struggling to recover emotionally from a brutal assault that killed her fiancé and left her in a coma, a radio personality begins a quest for vengeance against the perpetrators that leaves a bloody trail across New York City.

Title: Santa Claus
Description: With Merlin's aid, Santa Claus must defeat the evil machinations of the devil Pitch to ruin Christmas.

Title: Brief Crossing
Description: A young French man and an older English woman spend one night together on a ship.

Title: Friday the 13th: A New Beginning
Description: Still haunted by his past, Tommy Jarvis, who, as a child, killed Jason Voorhees, is sent to a secluded halfway house in the countryside, where the killing of a young man triggers a brutal series of murders in the area.

Title: The Island
Description: When his brother is killed, LAPD officer Mark leaves the city to return to the island he grew up on. Seeking answers and vengeance, he soon finds himself in a bloody battle with the corrupt tycoon who's taken over the island paradise.

Title: Veer-Zaara
Description: "Veer-Zaara" is a saga of love, separation, courage, and sacrifice. A love story that is an inspiration and will remain a legend forever.

Title: A Prophet
Description: A young Algerian man is sent to a French prison.

Title: Malice
Description: A tale about a happily married couple who would like to have children. Tracy teaches art, Andy's a college dean. Things are never the same after she is taken to hospital and operated upon by Jed, a "know all" doctor.

Title: Carpool
Description: When his wife falls sick, a father finds himself having to carpool for the neighborhood school children and being taken hostage by a bank robber.

Title: Summer Catch
Description: A rich girl whose family summers on Cape Cod has a romance with a local poor boy who hopes to become a major league baseball player.

Title: The Valet
Description: A movie star enlists a parking valet at a Beverly Hills restaurant to pose as her lover to cover for her relationship with a married man.

Title: Krampus: The Devil Returns
Description: Five years after the murder of his wife and disappearance of his daughter, former police officer Jeremy Duffin is brought back to help in the hunt for a yuletide monster that punishes children that have been "naughty." As the monster becomes more erratic and unpredictable, Jeremy learns the truth about the disappearance of his daughter and the fate that has been bestowed upon him by an unlikely source. Can Jeremy finally end the nightmare Christmas monster that has terrorized this town for years?

Title: Liberal Arts
Description: When 30-something Jesse returns to his alma mater for a professor's retirement party, he falls for Zibby, a college student, and is faced with a powerful attraction that springs up between them.

Title: Skyline
Description: Strange lights descend on the city of Los Angeles, drawing people outside like moths to a flame where an extraterrestrial force threatens to swallow the entire human population off the face of the Earth.

Title: That Touch of Mink
Description: A rich businessman and a young woman are attracted to each other, but he only wants an affair while she wants to save herself for marriage.

Title: Outland
Description: A federal marshal stationed at a mining colony on the Jupiter moon of Io uncovers a drug-smuggling conspiracy. He gets no help from the workers or authorities when he finds himself marked for murder.

Title: The Moon
Description: A man is left in space due to an unfortunate accident while another man on Earth struggles to bring him back safely.

Title: Stuart Little 2
Description: Stuart and Snowbell set out across town to rescue a friend.

Title: Raymond & Ray
Description: Half brothers Raymond and Ray reunite when their estranged father dies - and discover that his final wish was for them to dig his grave. Together, they process who they've become as men, both because of their father and in spite of him.

Title: The Oxford Murders
Description: At Oxford University, a professor and a grad student work together to try to stop a potential series of murders seemingly linked by mathematical symbols.

Title: Seventh Son
Description: When Mother Malkin, the queen of evil witches, escapes the pit she was imprisoned in by professional monster hunter Spook decades ago and kills his apprentice, he recruits young Tom, the seventh son of the seventh son, to help him.

Title: Inside the Yellow Cocoon Shell
Description: A man returns to his hometown, where he's haunted by past memories and desires.

Title: Arbitrage
Description: A troubled hedge fund magnate desperate to complete the sale of his trading empire makes an error that forces him to turn to an unlikely person for help.

Title: Purple Rain
Description: A young musician, tormented by an abusive situation at home, must contend with a rival singer, a burgeoning romance, and his own dissatisfied band, as his star begins to rise.

Title: Alligator
Description: A pet baby alligator is flushed down a toilet and survives in the city sewers. Twelve years later, it grows to an enormous size thanks to a diet of discarded laboratory dogs injected with growth hormones. Now, humans have entered the menu.

Title: Minamata
Description: War photographer W. Eugene Smith travels back to Japan where he documents the devastating effect of mercury poisoning in coastal communities.

Title: Burning Days
Description: Emre, a young prosecutor newly appointed to the small town of Yaniklar, finds himself being pulled into a political conflict during his first criminal investigation.

Title: Maggie's Plan
Description: Maggie wants to have a baby, raising him on her own, but when she gets romantically involved with John, a married man, things get complicated and all the balance of Maggie's plans may collapse.

Title: Vampires
Description: Recovering from an ambush that killed his entire team, a vengeful vampire slayer must retrieve an ancient Catholic relic that, should it be acquired by vampires, will allow them to walk in sunlight.

Title: Dunston Checks In
Description: A young boy befriends a larcenous orangutan in a luxury hotel.

Title: The Five Heartbeats
Description: The story of the rise and fall of an African American vocal group.

Title: Shelter
Description: Hannah and Tahir fall in love while homeless on the streets of New York. Shelter explores how they got there, and as we learn about their pasts we realize they need each other to build a future.

Title: The Three Musketeers
Description: Joined by an eager recruit to protect the King of France, three loyal swordsmen attempt to defeat an evil royal advisor and a seductive envoy plotting to overthrow the crown.

Title: Return to Sender
Description: A nurse living in small town goes on a blind date with a man who is not the person he says he is.

Title: Breath of Life
Description: Exploring life and destiny, where one must live to fulfill their purpose and cannot die until it is completed.

Title: Sorority Row
Description: A group of sorority sisters try to cover up the death of their house-sister after a prank gone wrong, only to be stalked by a serial killer.

Title: The Green Border
Description: Follows a family of Syrian refugees, an English teacher from Afghanistan and a border guard. They all meet on the Polish-Belarusian border during the most recent humanitarian crisis in Belarus.

Title: The Edge of Love
Description: Two feisty, free-spirited women are connected by the brilliant, charismatic poet who loves them both.

Title: In Harm's Way
Description: A Naval officer, reprimanded after Pearl Harbor, is later promoted to Rear Admiral and gets a second chance to prove himself against the Japanese.

Title: Becket
Description: King Henry II of England comes to terms with his affection for his close friend and confidant Thomas Becket, who finds his true honor by observing God's divine will rather than the King's.

Title: Repulsion
Description: A sex-repulsed woman who disapproves of her sister's boyfriend sinks into depression and has horrific visions of rape and violence.

Title: Satanic Hispanics
Description: When police break into a house in El Paso, they find it filled with dead Latinos and a lone survivor. Known as "El Viajero," he is taken to the police station for questioning.

Title: The Smurfs 2
Description: The Smurfs team up with their human friends to rescue Smurfette, who has been abducted by Gargamel, since she knows a secret spell that can turn the evil sorcerer's newest creation, creatures called "The Naughties", into real Smurfs.

Title: Flight of the Phoenix
Description: Survivors of a plane crash in the Mongolian desert work together to build a new plane.

Title: Immortal Beloved
Description: The life and death of the legendary Ludwig van Beethoven. Besides all the work he is known for, the composer once wrote a famous love letter to a nameless beloved, and the movie tries to find out who this beloved was--not easy, as Beethoven has had many women in his life.

Title: The Man with the Iron Heart
Description: As the German Fascists expand their borders, scorching Europe from end to end, two brave Czechs of the Resistance prepare for a suicide mission to assassinate Reinhard Heydrich, the hideous mastermind behind the "Final Solution".

Title: Mad About the Boy: The Noel Coward Story
Description: An exploration of Coward's expansive career which features credits across the stage and screen, including Brief Encounter, Blithe Spirit, and Private Lives.

Title: Cold War
Description: In the 1950s, a music director falls in love with a singer and tries to persuade her to flee communist Poland for France.

Title: Mighty Joe Young
Description: A legendary fifteen-foot tall mountain gorilla named Joe is taken to an animal sanctuary in California by zoologist Gregg O'Hara (Bill Paxton) and Jill Young (Charlize Theron), with whom he grew up. Poacher Strasser (Rade Serbedzija) returns from the past to seek vengeance on Joe.

Title: Gully Boy
Description: A coming-of-age story based on the lives of street rappers in Mumbai.

Title: Adult World
Description: A naive college graduate, Amy, who believes she's destined to be a great poet, begrudgingly accepts a job in a shop while she pursues a mentorship with reclusive writer Rat Billings.

Title: Heart and Souls
Description: An unhappy businessman finds a new sense of purpose after he's tasked with helping a quartet of ghosts fulfill their last wishes before moving on to the afterlife.

Title: Brigadoon
Description: Two Americans on a hunting trip in Scotland become lost. They encounter a small village, not on the map, called Brigadoon, in which people harbor a mysterious secret, and behave as if they were still living two hundred years in the past.

Title: Love Me
Description: A love story between a satellite and a buoy.

Title: The Kid
Description: The Tramp cares for an abandoned child, but events put their relationship in jeopardy.

Title: Elevator Game
Description: Supernatural horror, based on the eponymous online phenomenon, a ritual conducted in an elevator, in which players attempt to travel to another dimension using a set of rules that can be found online.

Title: The Wood
Description: While dealing with a friend's cold feet on his wedding day, a writer reminisces about his youth with his best friends.

Title: Rad
Description: The story of one young man, Cru Jones, who has the intensity and desire to win a BMX race called Helltrack.

Title: Grey Gardens
Description: Meet a mother and daughter, high-society dropouts, reclusive cousins of Jackie O., managing to thrive together amid the decay and disorder of their East Hampton, NY, mansion, making for an eerily ramshackle echo of the American Camelot.

Title: Nine Months
Description: When he finds out his longtime girlfriend is pregnant, a commitment-phobe realizes he might have to change his lifestyle for better or much, much worse.

Title: The Farm
Description: A young couple gets kidnapped and treated like farm animals after stopping at a roadside diner to eat meat.

Title: The Dogs of War
Description: Mercenary James Shannon, on a reconnaissance job to the African nation of Zangaro, is tortured and deported. He returns to lead a coup.

Title: The Stanford Prison Experiment
Description: In 1971, twenty-four male students are selected to take on randomly assigned roles of prisoners and guards in a mock prison situated in the basement of the Stanford psychology building.

Title: Y2K
Description: Two high school nobodies make the decision to crash the last major celebration before the new millennium on New Year's Eve 1999. The night becomes even crazier than they could have ever dreamed when the clock strikes midnight.

Title: How to Lose Friends & Alienate People
Description: A British writer struggles to fit in at a high-profile magazine in New York City.

Title: Charly
Description: An intellectually disabled man undergoes an experiment that gives him the intelligence of a genius.

Title: Bang Gang: A Modern Love Story
Description: In the well-to-do suburbs of a small town, a group of pretty average, well-adjusted sixteen and seventeen year olds are ordinary adolescents who take a singular path.

Title: Friendly Persuasion
Description: The pacifist attitude of a Quaker family is tested as a result of the American Civil War.

Title: Another Happy Christmas
Description: When the Eide family is gathered to celebrate Christmas together for the first time in years, it doesn't take long for old secrets to surface.

Title: Better Days
Description: While she copes the the pressures of her final examinations, a bullied teenage girl forms an unlikely friendship with a mysterious young man who protects her from her assailants.

Title: My Man Godfrey
Description: A scatterbrained socialite hires a vagrant as a family butler - but there's more to Godfrey than meets the eye.

Title: Pawn Sacrifice
Description: Set during the Cold War, American chess prodigy Bobby Fischer finds himself caught between two superpowers and his own struggles as he challenges the Soviet Empire.

Title: Memories
Description: An animated science fiction anthology from the visionary anime director, Katsuhiro Otomo.

Title: Outside the Wire
Description: In the near future, a drone pilot sent into a war zone finds himself paired with a top-secret android officer on a mission to stop a nuclear attack.

Title: Walking Tall
Description: Based on the life of Tennessee sheriff Buford Pusser, who almost single-handily cleaned up his small town of crime and corruption, but at a personal cost of his family life and nearly his own life.

Title: Jana Gana Mana
Description: As a college professor's brutal murder sparks student unrest, a cop launches an investigation while a lawyer seeks justice in the the courtroom.

Title: Melvin and Howard
Description: The story of hard-luck Melvin E. Dummar, who claimed to have received a will naming him an heir to the fortune of Howard Hughes.

Title: The Man Who Laughs
Description: When a proud noble refuses to kiss the hand of the despotic King James in 1690, he is cruelly executed and his son surgically disfigured.

Title: The Zookeeper's Wife
Description: Keepers of the Warsaw Zoo, Antonina and Jan Zabinski, must save hundreds of people and animals during the Nazi invasion in WWII Poland.

Title: The Devil's Backbone
Description: After Carlos - a 12-year-old whose father has died in the Spanish Civil War - arrives at an ominous boys' orphanage, he discovers the school is haunted and has many dark secrets which he must uncover.

Title: All Fun and Games
Description: A group of Salem teens discover a cursed knife that unleashes a demon that forces them to play gruesome, deadly versions of childhood games where there can be no winners, only survivors.

Title: Troll
Description: A wicked troll king in search of a mystical ring that will transform him to human form invades a San Francisco apartment complex where a powerful witch lives.

Title: Deseo
Description: A succession of erotic encounters weaved into a daisy chain of delightful sensuality. DESEO is a modern-day adaptation of Reigen, the controversial stage-play by the celebrated XIX century Austrian playwright, Arthur Schnitzler.

Title: Paranormal Activity 4
Description: It has been five years since the disappearance of Katie and Hunter, and a suburban family witness strange events in their neighborhood when a woman and a mysterious child move in.

Title: Shine
Description: Pianist David Helfgott, driven by his father and teachers, has a breakdown. Years later he returns to the piano, to popular if not critical acclaim.

Title: Serial Mom
Description: She's the perfect all-American parent: a great cook and homemaker, a devoted recycler, and a woman who'll literally kill to keep her children happy.

Title: The Face of the Faceless
Description: Based on Sr. Rani Maria, this tale depicts the trials and tribulations of a woman who rose above the boundaries of her religion, realized the universal oneness, and committed her life to women's empowerment.

Title: Sweet Charity
Description: Taxi dancer Charity continues to have Faith despite endless disappointments at its hands, and Hope that she will finally meet the man to romance her away from her sleazy life. Maybe, just maybe, handsome Oscar will be the one to do it.

Title: Sulis 1907
Description: In 1907, the miners in Sulitjelma in Fauske in Nordland made a famous rebellion against greedy mine owners.

Title: Lost in America
Description: A husband and wife in their 30s decide to quit their jobs, live as free spirits and cruise America in a Winnebago.

Title: Thank You for Your Service
Description: A group of U.S. soldiers returning from Iraq struggle to integrate back into family and civilian life, while living with the memory of a war that threatens to destroy them long after they've left the battlefield.

Title: No Small Affair
Description: 16-year-old Charles loves to photograph. A cute girl's photo ends up in his camera. He later sees the older Laura singing in a bar. He takes many more photos of her and ends seeing her again, wishing to help her career.

Title: It's Kind of a Funny Story
Description: A clinically-depressed teenager gets a new start after he checks himself into an adult psychiatric ward.

Title: Jagged Edge
Description: A wealthy woman is murdered in her beach house. The husband is allegedly knocked out first. He inherits all. He has a female ex criminal prosecutor represent him in court.

Title: McCabe & Mrs. Miller
Description: A gambler and a prostitute become business partners in a remote Old West mining town, and their enterprise thrives until a large corporation arrives on the scene.

Title: The Witcher: Nightmare of the Wolf
Description: Escaping from poverty to become a witcher, Vesemir slays monsters for coin and glory, but when a new menace rises, he must face the demons of his past.

Title: Biutiful
Description: A man dying of cancer tries his best to leave the world on his own terms.

Title: Cult of Chucky
Description: Chucky returns to terrorize his human victim, Nica. Meanwhile, the killer doll has some scores to settle with his old enemies, with the help of his former wife.

Title: The Escort
Description: Desperate for a good story, a sex-addicted journalist throws himself into the world of high-class escorts when he starts following a Stanford-educated prostitute.

Title: The Re-Education of Molly Singer
Description: To save her job, a young lawyer must go undercover, enrolling as a freshman at her old alma mater, in order to resuscitate the well being of her Boss' terribly awkward teenage son

Title: Karen
Description: Karen attempts to displace the new Black family that moved into the neighborhood, but they won't back down without a fight.

Title: Dear Zindagi
Description: Kaira is a budding cinematographer in search of a perfect life. Her encounter with Jug, an unconventional thinker, helps her gain a new perspective on life. She discovers that happiness is all about finding comfort in life's imperfections.

Title: Shelter
Description: When his college dreams are sidelined by family obligations, a young man finds comfort in surfing with his best friend's brother.

Title: The World of Henry Orient
Description: A mischievous, adventuresome fourteen-year-old girl and her best friend begin following an eccentric concert pianist around New York City after she develops a crush on him.

Title: Friendsgiving
Description: Molly and Abbey, along with their crew of close friends and acquaintances, host a dysfunctional, comical and chaotic Thanksgiving dinner.

Title: The Outrun
Description: After living life on the edge in London, Rona attempts to come to terms with her troubled past. She returns to the wild beauty of Scotland's Orkney Islands - where she grew up - hoping to heal. Adapted from Amy Liptrot's bestselling memoir

Title: Why Did I Get Married?
Description: The big-screen adaptation of Perry's stage play about the trials of marriage and what happens to one family when a sexy young temptress arrives on the scene.

Title: Tuck Everlasting
Description: A young woman meets and falls in love with a young man who is part of a family of immortals.

Title: Sissi - Schicksalsjahre einer Kaiserin
Description: The final film in a highly romanticized trilogy about Elisabeth "Sissi" of Austria finds the young empress traveling throughout Europe.

Title: The Alamo
Description: Based on the 1836 standoff between a group of Texan and Tejano men, led by Davy Crockett and Jim Bowie, and Mexican dictator Santa Anna's forces at the Alamo in San Antonio Texas.

Title: Conjuring Kannappan
Description: A man comes begins to have nightmares where he experiences things in sleep have an effect on him in real life, too. But as his derangement spreads across his family and friends, they decide to go to the root of the cause.

Title: Caché
Description: A married couple is terrorized by a series of surveillance videotapes left on their front porch.

Title: Antiporno
Description: Japan's oldest major movie studio asks a batch of venerable filmmakers to revive its high-brow soft-core Roman Porno series.

Title: Silent Running
Description: In a future where all flora is extinct on Earth, an astronaut is given orders to destroy the last of Earth's botany, kept in a greenhouse aboard a spacecraft.

Title: Joe Kidd
Description: An ex-bounty hunter reluctantly helps a wealthy landowner and his henchmen track down a Mexican revolutionary leader.

Title: Reagan
Description: A drama based on the life of Ronald Reagan, from his childhood to his time in the oval office.

Title: Surrounded
Description: Former Buffalo Soldier Mo Washington travels West to lay claim on a gold mine. After her stagecoach is ambushed, Mo is tasked with holding a dangerous outlaw captive and must survive the day when the bandit's gang tries to free him.

Title: High Art
Description: A young female intern at a small magazine company and a drug-addicted lesbian photographer slowly fall in love while exploiting each other to advance their respective careers.

Title: Heidi
Description: A story of a young girl who lives in the Swiss Alps with her goat herding Grandfather.

Title: Maggie
Description: A teenage girl in the Midwest becomes infected by an outbreak of a disease that slowly turns the infected into cannibalistic zombies. During her transformation, her loving father stays by her side.

Title: Final Summer
Description: In the aftermath of a tragedy at a summer camp, a group of camp counselors find themselves fighting for their lives against a masked killer.

Title: Four Good Days
Description: A mother helps her daughter work through four crucial days of recovery from substance abuse.

Title: She's the One
Description: The love lives of two brothers, Mickey and Francis, interconnect as Francis cheats on his wife with Mickey's ex-girlfriend, while Mickey impulsively marries a stranger.

Title: The Idiots
Description: The group of people gather at the house in Copenhagen suburb to break all the limitations and to bring out the "inner idiot" in themselves.

Title: Sleuth
Description: A man who loves games and theater invites his wife's lover to meet him, setting up a battle of wits with potentially deadly results.

Title: My Bloody Valentine
Description: A decades-old folk tale surrounding a deranged murderer killing those who celebrate Valentine's Day turns out to be true to legend when a group defies the killer's order and people start turning up dead.

Title: Down Periscope
Description: Lt. Cmdr. Tom Dodge is assigned as Captain to the USS Stingray, an old diesel driven submarine that has seen better days.

Title: Someone Great
Description: After a devastating break up on the eve of her cross-country move, Jenny enjoys one last NYC adventure with her two best pals. Someone Great is a romantic comedy about love, loss, growth and the everlasting bond of female friendship.

Title: Vindicta
Description: When a city is terrorized by a sadistic serial killer, a seasoned detective and a newly recruited paramedic discover the key to stopping the bloodshed lies in unlocking the truth of their own haunted pasts.

Title: Cosmopolis
Description: Riding across Manhattan in a stretch limo in order to get a haircut, a 28-year-old billionaire asset manager's day devolves into an odyssey with a cast of characters that start to tear his world apart.

Title: The Collection
Description: A man who escapes from the vicious grips of the serial killer known as "The Collector" is then forced to help rescue an innocent girl from the killer's booby-trapped lair.

Title: Happy Death Day 2U
Description: Tree Gelbman discovers that dying over and over was surprisingly easier than the dangers that lie ahead.

Title: Chances Are
Description: A reincarnated man unknowingly falls in love with his own daughter from his previous life. Once he realizes this, he tries to end their relationship before angels erase his memory.

Title: Prom Pact
Description: Follows the main character, a feminist who doesn't believe in the idea of falling in love, especially in heteronormative love, but then she falls and there's undeniable chemistry.

Title: Every Secret Thing
Description: A detective looks to unravel a mystery surrounding missing children and the prime suspects: two young women who, seven years ago, were put away for an infant's death.

Title: The 39 Steps
Description: A man in London tries to help a counter-espionage agent, but when the agent is killed and the man stands accused, he must go on the run to save himself and stop a spy ring that is trying to steal top-secret information.

Title: Lux Æterna
Description: Two actresses, Béatrice Dalle and Charlotte Gainsbourg, are on a film set telling stories about witches - but that's not all. 'Lux Æterna' is also an essay on cinema, the love of film, and on-set hysterics.

Title: Stir Crazy
Description: Set up and wrongfully accused, two best friends are sent to prison for a crime they didn't commit. However, no prison cell can keep them locked in a cage.

Title: The Forest
Description: A young woman's desperate search for her twin sister brings her to a ghost-filled stretch of wilderness known as the 'Suicide Forest.'

Title: Show Me Love
Description: Two teenage girls in small-town Sweden. Elin is beautiful, popular, and bored with life. Agnes is friendless, sad, and secretly in love with Elin.

Title: Den ofrivillige golfaren
Description: I bet anyone can get better at golf than you are in one week, a golfer says to her golfing businessman for a boyfriend in a quarrel. Unfortunately Stig-Helmer is standing nearby when the boyfriend accepts the bet, and he is chosen to be the competitor. Stig-Helmer has never played the game before, but his Norwegian friend Ole promises to help him.

Title: Black Emanuelle
Description: While on assignment in Nairobi, a photojournalist questions her racial and sexual identity when she engages in affairs with her wealthy hosts.

Title: Secretariat
Description: Penny Chenery Tweedy and colleagues guide her long-shot but precocious stallion to set, in 1973, the unbeaten record for winning the Triple Crown.

Title: Child's Play 2
Description: While Andy's mother is admitted to a psychiatric hospital, the young boy is placed in foster care, and Chucky, determined to claim Andy's soul, is not far behind.

Title: The World According to Garp
Description: A struggling young writer finds his life and work dominated by his unfaithful wife and his radical feminist mother, whose best-selling manifesto turns her into a cultural icon.

Title: Tenebrae
Description: An American writer in Rome is stalked and harassed by a serial killer who is murdering everyone associated with his work on his latest book.

Title: Private Life
Description: An author is undergoing multiple fertility therapies to get pregnant, putting her relationship with her husband on edge.

Title: Second Act
Description: A big-box store worker reinvents her life and her life-story and shows Madison Avenue what street smarts can do.

Title: A Christmas Vintage
Description: Samantha goes home to help her love struck sister, Emily, during the holidays. She discovers that Emily and Tony can not be together unless Samantha attracts and dates the unpleasant Parker Williams, an owner of a competing winery.

Title: Clue
Description: Based on the Hasbro board game, a band of strangers frantically try to figure out who is the murderer among them.

Title: The Apartment
Description: A recently engaged man sees a former lover and becomes obsessed with meeting her again.

Title: Casualties of War
Description: During the Vietnam War, a soldier finds himself the outsider of his own squad when they unnecessarily kidnap a female villager.

Title: Mighty Aphrodite
Description: When he discovers his adopted son is a genius, a New York sportswriter seeks out the boy's birth mother: a ditzy porn star and prostitute.

Title: Christmas Miracle
Description: Due to a road closure, eight strangers must take refuge in an abandoned church during a storm. They learn how to manage through various dilemmas by working together.

Title: Step Up 3D
Description: A tight-knit group of New York City street dancers find themselves pitted against the world's best hip hop dancers in a high-stakes showdown.

Title: The Enforcer
Description: An enforcer has to sacrifice everything to save a young girl he has befriended from his femme fatale boss who is involved in cybersex trafficking.

Title: She's Having a Baby
Description: Young newlyweds find out just how unprepared they are for their future together.

Title: Fall
Description: A young man named Edmar falls madly in love with Karisma, a barrio lass. Will he still love her if he finds out Karisma's deepest darkest secret?

Title: Tigerland
Description: A group of recruits go through Advanced Infantry Training at Fort Polk, Louisiana's infamous Tigerland, last stop before Vietnam for tens of thousands of young men in 1971.

Title: The Two Jakes
Description: The sequel to Chinatown (1974) finds J.J. "Jake" Gittes investigating adultery and murder, and the money that comes from oil.

Title: The Subject Was Roses
Description: A young man returning home from World War II finds himself caught up in his parents' turbulent relationship.

Title: Shameless
Description: A young man entertains an unhealthy desire for his older and unstable half-sister.

Title: Southern Comfort
Description: During a routine exercise, a team of National Guards are threatened by angry and violent locals.

Title: Batman: The Killing Joke
Description: As Batman hunts for the escaped Joker, the Clown Prince of Crime attacks the Gordon family to prove a diabolical point mirroring his own fall into madness.

Title: Warpath
Description: John Vickers joins Custer's cavalry regiment seeking private revenge.

Title: Don't Look Away
Description: It doesn't move, it doesn't think, it just kills. For one young woman, a chance encounter with this supernatural entity proves devastating. Frankie learns that once you see the mannequin, there may be no end in sight, except for your own.

Title: The Man with the Answers
Description: A former Greek diving champion and an eccentric German student take an adventurous road-trip of rediscovery from Bari to Bavaria.

Title: Little Nemo: Adventures in Slumberland
Description: Each night, young Nemo goes to Slumberland and has adventures and befriends the king of Slumberland, Morpheus. But one night Nemo discovers Nightmare Land, and the evil nightmare king, throwing Slumberland and Nemo himself into danger.

Title: Becoming Jane
Description: A biographical portrait of a pre-fame Jane Austen and her romance with a young Irishman.

Title: The Fog
Description: A thick mist full of vengeful spirits haunts a prosperous island town off the coast of Oregon, as its inhabitants try to learn their town's dark secret in order to stop it.

Title: Gambit
Description: An art curator decides to seek revenge on his abusive boss by conning him into buying a fake Monet, but his plan requires the help of an eccentric and unpredictable Texas rodeo queen.

Title: Untitled Guy Ritchie's Project
Description: Revolves around two extraction specialists who have to designate a route of escape for a senior female negotiator.

Title: Sam & Kate
Description: A son returns to his small hometown to take care of his ailing father.

Title: The Command
Description: The 2000 K-141 Kursk submarine disaster is followed by governmental negligence. As the sailors fight for survival, their families desperately battle political obstacles and impossible odds to save them.

Title: Ninjababy
Description: Astronaut, forest-keeper, cartoonist. Young Rakel has a whole lot of other plans than becoming a mother. She would rather party, get drunk or stoned instead of sitting hours on the toilet. But she can't ignore it. Is it her or the baby?

Title: Mary Magdalene
Description: Twelve men heard and spread the message of Jesus. Only one woman understood it.

Title: Lights Out
Description: A drifting ex-soldier turns underground fighter with the help of a just released ex-con, pitting them both against corrupt cops and hired killers gunning for them and all those they care about.

Title: Scandal
Description: Based on the Profumo Scandal of 1963, an affair between an exotic dancer and the Minister of War shakes up the British government.

Title: Ferry
Description: Ruthless Ferry Bouman is sent to his native region of Brabant by his boss Brink to avenge an attack on their gang. When he meets lovely Danielle and old family feuds resurface, Brabant starts to pierce his steel armour.

Title: Child's Play
Description: A mother gives her 13-year-old son a toy doll for his birthday, unaware of its more sinister nature.

Title: Invasion of the Bee Girls
Description: A powerful cosmic force is turning Earth women into queen bees who kill men by wearing them out sexually.

Title: Flickering Lights
Description: A gang of 4 Danish criminals are ordered by Færingen to steal a bag from a safe. When they see DKK4,000,000 in the bag, they keep it for themselves and head for Spain. They end up in a ruin of an old restaurant on Jutland and renovate it.

Title: I Am All Girls
Description: A special crimes investigator forms an unlikely bond with a serial killer to bring down a global child sex trafficking syndicate.

Title: The Sleeping Dictionary
Description: A young Englishman is sent to Malaysian Borneo in the 1930s to stay with a tribe as UK's colonial representative. A local woman (J.Alba) helps him understand local tradition and language. He falls in love with her etc. despite the taboo.

Title: The Painted Veil
Description: A British medical doctor fights a cholera epidemic in a small Chinese village, while being trapped at home in a loveless marriage to an unfaithful wife.

Title: Down with Love
Description: In 1962 New York City, love blossoms between a playboy journalist and a feminist advice author.

Title: Humanist Vampire Seeking Consenting Suicidal Person
Description: A young woman vampire is unable to kill to meet her need for blood, but may have found a solution in a young man with suicidal tendencies.

Title: Pingpong
Description: After his father's suicide, confused angsty 16 year old Paul goes to stay with his uncle's family. His uncle's wife is also unhappy with her life, so she and Paul have sex and only end up feeling even worse afterwards. Things get ugly.

Title: The Debt
Description: In 1965, three Mossad Agents cross into East Berlin to apprehend a notorious Nazi war criminal. Thirty years later, the secrets the Agents share come back to haunt them.

Title: Fly Away Home
Description: A father and daughter decide to attempt to lead a flock of orphaned Canada Geese south by air.

Title: Unsane
Description: A young woman is involuntarily committed to a mental institution, where she is confronted by her greatest fear - but is it real or a product of her delusion?

Title: Birthright Outlaw
Description: A daughter kidnapped. A hidden past revealed. A seemingly futile chance at rescue. Now, Rev. Jeremiah Jacobs and his wife Martha must overcome the lies of the past to find their Hope for the future.

Title: Proximity
Description: A young NASA JPL scientist is abducted by extraterrestrials, but when no one believes his story he becomes obsessed with finding proof, which leads him on a journey of discovery.

Title: Tiger Zinda Hai
Description: Inspired by real events, Tiger Zinda Hai is a sequel to the blockbuster Ek Tha Tiger, and an espionage action drama that follows a daring rescue mission in Iraq.

Title: The Castle
Description: A working-class family from Melbourne, Australia fights city hall after being told they must vacate their beloved family home to allow for infrastructural expansion.

Title: 20,000 Species of Bees
Description: During a summer in a village house linked to beekeeping, an eight-year-old and her mother experience revelations that will change their lives forever.

Title: Quiz Show
Description: A young lawyer, Richard Goodwin, investigates a potentially fixed game show. Charles Van Doren, a big time show winner, is under Goodwin's investigation.

Title: Rosaline
Description: A comedic retelling of Shakespeare's "Romeo and Juliet," told from the point of view of Romeo's jilted ex, Rosaline, the woman Romeo first claims to love before he falls for Juliet.

Title: My Little Pony: A New Generation
Description: After the time of the Mane 6, Sunny--a young Earth Pony--and her new Unicorn friend Izzy explore their world and strive to restore Harmony to Equestria.

Title: How It Ends
Description: In this feel-good apocalyptic comedy, Liza (Zoe Lister-Jones) embarks on a hilarious journey through LA in hopes of making it to her last party before it all ends, running into an eclectic cast of characters along the way.

Title: Repo Men
Description: Set in the near future when artificial organs can be bought on credit, it revolves around a man who struggles to make the payments on a heart he has purchased. He must therefore go on the run before said ticker is repossessed.

Title: Fight Club
